============================================================
PHASE 4 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the automation layer for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Create Friday Agent as automation coordinator
2. Create scheduler system
3. Add recurring job support
4. Add manual job run/pause/resume/delete controls
5. Add predefined system jobs
6. Add IoT adapter interface
7. Add Tapo Smart Plug adapter shell
8. Add dry-run IoT action mode
9. Add Windows NSSM service installer
10. Add scheduler API endpoints
11. Add automation audit logs
12. Add tests for scheduler and IoT safety

IMPORTANT:
- Automation must default to safe dry-run mode.
- IoT power actions must not run for real unless IOT_DRY_RUN=false.
- Trading jobs must respect Guardian risk system.
- Scheduler must not bypass risk controls.
- Do not hardcode Tapo credentials or device IP.
- Do not implement real destructive power-cycle logic without safety confirmation flags.
- Use mock adapters when external dependencies are unavailable.

