============================================================
IOT ADAPTER REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/iot/base.py

Define:

class IoTAdapter:
  - get_status(device_alias: str) -> IoTActionResult
  - turn_on(device_alias: str) -> IoTActionResult
  - turn_off(device_alias: str) -> IoTActionResult
  - power_cycle(device_alias: str) -> IoTActionResult

Create:

backend/app/iot/tapo_adapter.py

Implement:

TapoAdapter

Requirements:

- Reads TAPO_USERNAME, TAPO_PASSWORD, TAPO_DEVICE_IP, TAPO_DEVICE_ALIAS from config.
- Must support dry-run.
- If credentials are missing, must return safe dry-run/mock result.
- Do not crash if real Tapo library is missing.
- Leave clean placeholder integration for future real Tapo API.
- For power_cycle:
  - In dry-run mode, simulate turn_off → wait → turn_on
  - In real mode, require confirmation
  - Never power-cycle without confirmation if IOT_REQUIRE_CONFIRMATION=true

============================================================
IOT SERVICE REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/iot/iot_service.py

Implement:

IoTService

Methods:

- get_status(device_alias: str | None = None) -> IoTActionResult
- execute(action: IoTAction) -> IoTActionResult
- turn_on(device_alias: str, confirmation: bool = false) -> IoTActionResult
- turn_off(device_alias: str, confirmation: bool = false) -> IoTActionResult
- power_cycle(device_alias: str, confirmation: bool = false) -> IoTActionResult

Safety rules:

- IOT_DRY_RUN=true must simulate all actions.
- If IOT_ENABLED=false, block real action.
- If IOT_REQUIRE_CONFIRMATION=true and confirmation=false, block real action.
- Emit events:
  - iot.action.requested
  - iot.action.simulated
  - iot.action.completed
  - iot.action.blocked
  - iot.action.failed

============================================================
SCHEDULER API REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/api/scheduler.py

Required endpoints:

1. GET /api/scheduler/status

Returns scheduler status.

2. GET /api/scheduler/jobs

Returns all jobs.

3. POST /api/scheduler/jobs

Request:

{
  "name": "Manual XAU scan",
  "job_type": "trading_scan",
  "schedule_type": "manual",
  "payload": {
    "symbol": "XAUUSD",
    "timeframe": "M5",
    "dry_run": true
  },
  "enabled": true
}

4. POST /api/scheduler/jobs/{job_id}/run

Runs job manually.

5. POST /api/scheduler/jobs/{job_id}/pause

Pauses job.

6. POST /api/scheduler/jobs/{job_id}/resume

Resumes job.

7. DELETE /api/scheduler/jobs/{job_id}

Deletes job.

8. GET /api/scheduler/runs

Returns recent job runs.

9. GET /api/scheduler/runs/{job_id}

Returns runs for one job.

============================================================
IOT API REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

backend/app/api/iot.py

Required endpoints:

1. GET /api/iot/status

Returns device status or dry-run mock status.

2. POST /api/iot/action

Request:

{
  "device_alias": "zdash-power-node",
  "action": "status",
  "confirmation": false,
  "payload": {}
}

3. POST /api/iot/power-cycle

Request:

{
  "device_alias": "zdash-power-node",
  "confirmation": false
}

Behavior:
- In dry-run mode: simulate and return ok.
- In real mode without confirmation: block.
- With confirmation and correct config: call adapter.

============================================================
API RESPONSE FORMAT
============================================================

All endpoints must use existing standard response shape:

Success:

{
  "ok": true,
  "data": {},
  "error": null,
  "timestamp": "ISO_DATE"
}

Error:

{
  "ok": false,
  "data": null,
  "error": {
    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
    "message": "Human readable message"
  },
  "timestamp": "ISO_DATE"
}

