============================================================
WINDOWS NSSM SERVICE SCRIPT REQUIREMENTS
============================================================

Create:

scripts/install-nssm-service.ps1

The script must:

1. Require PowerShell 5+
2. Check if nssm.exe exists in PATH
3. Read environment variables:
   - NSSM_SERVICE_NAME
   - NSSM_DISPLAY_NAME
   - NSSM_DESCRIPTION
   - NSSM_BACKEND_HOST
   - NSSM_BACKEND_PORT
4. Detect backend path
5. Detect Python executable
6. Install service:
   - app path: python
   - args: -m uvicorn app.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
   - startup directory: backend path
7. Configure:
   - display name
   - description
   - restart on failure
   - stdout log path
   - stderr log path
8. Print commands to start/stop service
9. Never embed secrets

Create:

scripts/uninstall-nssm-service.ps1

The script must:

1. Check if service exists
2. Stop service if running
3. Remove service using NSSM
4. Print result

